queries: You use this sign when you are thinking of one thing being less than another.
verblex: 1. Of two or more things, to be different in size, strength, or ability with each having more or less of one quality than the others. English = (be) unequal.
2. To treat people in different ways, for example by giving some people more money or privileges than others. English = (be) unequal.
nomlex: 1. The difference in size or amount of two or more things. English = inequality.
2. The difference in social status, wealth, or opportunity between groups in a society. English = inequality.
